      "content": "The French Revolution, which started in 1789, was a pivotal moment in modern history, driven by the widespread discontent with social inequality and economic hardship. At the helm was King Louis XVI, whose inability to address these issues further exacerbated the crisis. The Storming of the Bastille on July 14, 1789, marked a turning point, as the people's desire for change culminated in the adoption of the Declaration of the Rights of Man and of the Citizen in August 1789. However, the Reign of Terror, led by the influential Maximilien Robespierre, from 1793 to 1794, brought about a period of extreme violence and repression. Ultimately, Napoleon Bonaparte's rise to power in 1799 brought an end to the revolution, marking a new era in French history.",
